McDonald's moved into new markets, opening restaurants in Korea, Yugoslavia, the first
communist country to get a McDonald's, the Soviet Union, and China. The opening day
crowds were large and  enthusiastic about the flavor of the Big Mac. The openings came
after years of negotiations which, in some cases, stipulated that McDonald's buy its
supplies locally.</SUM>
